Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.02,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a fairy tale
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:05.44,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sign the story has reached its end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:08.36,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Like a single passage taken from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.36,0:00:09.98,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,A journey that was too long
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.98,0:00:12.32,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Of the evil that once cast a shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.32,0:00:14.66,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Across this land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:16.99,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the memories of the short journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.99,0:00:19.45,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With the hero who defeated it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.24,0:00:29.21,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,473)\blur0.25\fs25\fnGeorgia\fsp3.9\pos(322,230)\c&HFFFCFE&\t(989,4326,\c&HEFC777&)\t(6411,6745,\c&HEAC732&)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.46,0:00:31.76,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The story ends
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.76,0:00:34.26,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And the hero goes to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.26,0:00:37.09,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Leaving this land with
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.09,0:00:38.76,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Days of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:41.27,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time heartlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.27,0:00:43.43,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Makes people forget
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.43,0:00:46.23,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even the tracks left behind by his life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:48.02,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Begin to rust
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.02,0:00:49.86,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Just the same
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.86,0:00:52.15,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Your words and wishes and courage
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.15,0:00:55.49,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Are still inside of me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.49,0:00:57.36,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And they live on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.16,0:00:59.91,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,We chose the same path
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.91,0:01:02.04,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,That's all it was supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.04,0:01:03.58,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it that at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.58,0:01:07.83,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to understand the reason for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.83,0:01:09.21,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,The tears that fall down my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.21,0:01:10.29,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.29,0:01:12.67,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,If I retrace the journey we walked together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.67,0:01:16.22,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you're not there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.22,0:01:17.89,Songs_OP,OP LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'll be able to find it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.98,0:01:35.99,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}28 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nat the Granz Channel, located in the central lands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:41.78,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,This area has always been \Ndifficult to navigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.78,0:01:44.66,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,so all kinds of things wash up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.91,0:01:49.92,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,It used to be that the entire village \Nhelped clean up the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.92,0:01:53.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But now you don't have enough people, \Nso it lies neglected.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:01:58.01,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,These waters used to be beautifully clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.43,0:02:00.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.56,0:02:06.43,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,How about this as payment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.40,0:02:12.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a book written by \NFlamme the Legendary Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:14.40,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.19,0:02:17.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the only grimoire \Nyou have in your village?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.86,0:02:18.74,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:23.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. We'll clean up the area for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.45,0:02:30.46,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That grimoire is a fake, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:34.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see you've been studying like \NI told you to. Good girl, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:40.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Books attributed to Flamme are never real. \NThis is just another poor imitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:43.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you accept the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:46.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,To help someone in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.10,0:02:49.48,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I find that hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.90,0:02:54.27,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I'm doing this for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.86,0:02:59.61,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like we've got another \Nlong stay ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:17.80,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for being such a \Nregular customer, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:20.17,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,I threw in an extra one for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.17,0:03:21.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:24.22,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,It's been three months already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:26.26,Default,SHOPKEEPER,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gotten used to the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:27.06,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.06,0:03:31.98,Default,OLD WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shore gets cold this \Ntime of year. Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:37.86,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It's winter already.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:44.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.78,0:03:47.62,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This place is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.12,0:03:50.62,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I just tidied up yesterday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:56.38,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, it's morning. Please wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.35,0:04:09.64,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go clean up the shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.75,0:04:35.29,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.71,0:04:39.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:41.05,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.42,0:04:46.55,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you actually a very sloppy person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.93,0:04:52.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Every morning I wake you up, feed you \Nbreakfast, and help you get dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:56.06,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm practically your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.31,0:04:58.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can do all that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:05:01.69,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But then you'd sleep until noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:02.99,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:06.07,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've already given up hope, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.70,0:05:08.16,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:11.95,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,How did you manage traveling \Nwith the hero's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:15.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't anyone there \Nto look after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:17.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I overslept all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.13,0:05:20.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,And you never got in trouble for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:23.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I did, just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:29.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Just once? They must have been very tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:30.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They were a whole different breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.35,0:05:34.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Heiter sometimes clicked his tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.89,0:05:35.77,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:37.39,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.39,0:05:39.10,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I understand how you feel, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.57,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like they were rather upset with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:57.71,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,How is the cleanup coming along?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.62,0:06:01.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We have about a third of it left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.71,0:06:04.88,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you'll be done in time \Nfor the New Year's Festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:06.17,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just barely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:13.14,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I hope you'll be able to watch \Nthe sunrise this time, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.15,0:06:26.24,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is the beach cleanup related to \Nthe New Year's Festival somehow?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:31.62,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,In this village, it's customary to watch the \Nsunrise on the day of the New Year's Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.87,0:06:37.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They say it's beautiful how the light \Nreflects off the clear waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.12,0:06:40.50,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't seen it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.08,0:06:43.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'd be able \Nto wake up that early?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.21,0:06:49.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry. We don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:31.93,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,No problems with the water quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.30,0:07:35.01,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We managed to finish by the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.47,0:07:37.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It hardly looks like the same beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:41.52,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.98,0:07:45.36,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be joining us for the \NNew Year's Festival, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.36,0:07:46.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.44,0:07:48.40,Default,VILLAGE CHIEF,0000,0000,0000,,We'd love to have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.49,0:07:52.24,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Have you lost your mind, Ms. Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:54.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to wake up before the sun rises.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:56.24,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:58.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. I just need \Nto stay up all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.45,0:08:01.91,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're that desperate to see the sunrise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.41,0:08:06.92,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I'm not interested, \Nwhich is why I want to see it for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:09.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:11.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I suppose you wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.56,0:08:23.19,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you come to the \NNew Year's Festival, Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.64,0:08:28.44,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,The shock was so great, \Nit left Heiter bedridden. Poor guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:31.78,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,He's just out of commission \Nbecause he drank too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:35.03,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem? \NThe rest of you got to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:39.41,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted you to enjoy it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.70,0:08:44.25,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a sunrise. \NI doubt I'd enjoy it much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.25,0:08:46.58,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,No, you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:47.54,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:50.88,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're that kind of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.76,0:08:56.05,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.76,0:08:59.14,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.14,0:09:03.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, wake up. \NYou'll be late for the New Year's Festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.39,0:09:04.81,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.81,0:09:06.56,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling "Mother"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.36,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.03,0:09:16.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Fern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:35.30,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's certainly pretty, but it wasn't \Nworth waking up early for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.22,0:09:39.05,DefaultItalics,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Himmel didn't understand me after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:42.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern, I'm going home so I can go back to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.47,0:09:46.98,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, it's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:49.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.06,0:09:52.82,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a sunrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:57.99,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But you seem to be enjoying \Nyourself a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.41,0:10:01.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you're smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.50,0:10:14.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have been able to see \Nthis sunrise if I'd been on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.63,0:10:19.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. After all, you can't \Nget out of bed by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:23.89,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(379,270.5)}Episode 4: The Land Where Souls Rest
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:27.39,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Are these for your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:29.48,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:32.98,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,My village was attacked by demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:37.40,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.36,0:10:39.95,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:42.91,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,People return to nothingness when they die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.91,0:10:44.91,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,No, they go to Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:46.91,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Until several thousand years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.92,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,the commonly held belief \Nwas that there was no afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:52.75,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Dwarves value tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.17,0:10:56.55,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm skeptical about the idea \Nof a heaven myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.55,0:11:01.80,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but since current magics can't \Nobserve the souls of the dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:04.35,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,its existence can't be proven or disproven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:06.89,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it matters either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:11.90,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I don't care \Nif it exists or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:15.40,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Should a man of the cloth be saying that, \Nyou corrupt priest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:21.24,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,But even if it doesn't exist, \NI believe it should.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.20,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.86,0:11:25.83,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's more convenient that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.37,0:11:29.50,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,All those people doing their best \Nto live deserve something better
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.50,0:11:31.75,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,than nothingness awaiting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.71,0:11:38.67,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I prefer to think they get to \Nlive the good life in Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:45.43,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,That certainly is more convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.06,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we pray?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:48.64,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.36,0:12:01.53,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(738,645)\blur0.2\pos(588.5,126)}28 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Bredt region, located in the central lands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.45,0:12:06.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen, I'm here to hang out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:11.04,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You act like it hasn't been thirty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:13.67,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's a mere thirty years?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.08,0:12:17.50,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:22.42,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you'd take on an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:27.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen, is there anything you need help with?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:33.52,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, I heard you asked \NHeiter the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.98,0:12:36.19,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not on my deathbed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.69,0:12:38.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:41.19,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Because we wrote to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.19,0:12:43.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're more conscientious than you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.95,0:12:46.95,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're just too indifferent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.95,0:12:50.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So, do you need help with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.29,0:12:55.83,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Voll Basin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:57.50,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This place brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:12:59.96,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.96,0:13:01.00,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:05.43,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,"A long time," she said. \NHow long must that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.80,0:13:08.72,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps she came here in prehistoric times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:11.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even I've lived that long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.77,0:13:16.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are we looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.81,0:13:19.94,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,The notes of Flamme the Legendary Mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.90,0:13:26.49,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. You know most of Flamme's \Nsupposed writings are fake, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:28.37,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I have a lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.87,0:13:35.46,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiter deduced the location from records \Non Flamme left in the holy city.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:40.21,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Her genuine notes are located \Nsomewhere in Voll Basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:44.59,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you must know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.47,0:13:49.55,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That corrupt priest. \NHe'd gotten that far in his research?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:54.18,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. We'll begin by searching \Nfor a large tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.64,0:13:56.39,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,A large tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.77,0:14:00.06,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous. There are tons of trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:04.32,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose you have \Nall the time in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:05.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:09.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But Fern wouldn't like that, \Nso I'll try to finish quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:15.41,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Let's search as efficiently as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:19.50,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You've changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.50,0:14:24.46,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You never cared about \Nother people's time before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:27.88,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern is scary when she's mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.13,0:14:31.76,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then I should watch myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:06.80,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:11.09,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a large tree to the west \Ngrowing over some ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:13.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:14.85,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:22.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Why did you decide to \Nlook for Flamme's notes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.82,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Because I felt sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.23,0:15:27.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:31.78,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I felt sorry for you and Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.57,0:15:34.82,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,On that day thirty years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:38.79,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,you said you wished you'd gotten \Nto know Himmel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:44.04,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You should tell Himmel himself that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.42,0:15:52.93,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,They say the notes of Flamme the Legendary \NMage describe her conversing with the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.26,0:15:58.18,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's just a fairy tale. \NBesides, I don't want to see him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.47,0:16:02.02,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,All magic started as fairy tales.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:05.61,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,And don't you want to know more about Himmel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:09.57,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I talked it over with Heiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:15.82,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,We were sure you had regrets, \Nso we wanted to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.83,0:16:30.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, both the tree and ruins \Nare protected by a powerful barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:39.31,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even after a thousand years, I'm still \Ndancing in the palm of my master's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.60,0:16:44.23,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,How's that little sapling going to keep watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.23,0:16:45.81,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sell it short.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:52.61,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Once it grows, it'll still be protecting \Nthis place a thousand years from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.07,0:16:55.61,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be dead by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:16:58.91,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,But you won't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:05.25,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, you'll make a terrible mistake \Nand wish you'd gotten to know people better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:09.13,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you wish I knew you better? \NAre you being needy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:10.55,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:13.88,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,When that happens, return to this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.67,0:17:20.01,Flashback,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Then I, Flamme the Legendary Mage, \Nwill help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:37.28,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Those are Flamme's notes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:40.37,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are they real?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.78,0:17:42.24,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They're real.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.66,0:17:44.25,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.75,0:17:47.79,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren was Flamme's best student.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:53.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Flamme the Legendary Mage is an ancient hero \Nwho's written about in magical history.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:57.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you haven't been \Naround since prehistoric times?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:18:01.30,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Does it say anything about \Nspeaking to the dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:04.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's already opened to that very page.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:09.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Did she know a thousand years ago \Nthat I'd come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.56,0:18:13.11,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What an unpleasant woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.15,0:18:16.82,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,"On the northernmost end of the continent..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:21.07,DefaultItalics,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,I arrived at the place the people \Nof this world call heaven:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:25.45,DefaultItalics,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Aureole, the land where souls rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.12,0:18:29.08,DefaultItalics,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,Many souls gather there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.54,0:18:32.63,DefaultItalics,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,and I spoke with friends \Nwho once fought alongside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:37.09,DefaultItalics,FLAMME,0000,0000,0000,,This discovery of the century...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:40.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,"...will propel research on souls forward."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:44.85,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose it's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:48.02,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? She was an irresponsible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.56,0:18:50.19,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Heaven exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:53.69,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's more convenient if it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:59.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. Perhaps I should \Nbelieve in it for once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:03.20,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Where exactly is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.62,0:19:05.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:09.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The northern continent... Ende.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:11.12,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ende?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.12,0:19:12.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:16.21,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's where the Demon King's \Ncastle is located now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:20.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But why there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:22.34,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:27.10,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You must find Aureole and speak with Himmel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.56,0:19:31.98,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd help me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.23,0:19:36.98,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You've learned some cunning tricks, Eisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:39.65,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Heiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.49,0:19:43.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. I didn't have a particular \Ndestination anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.20,0:19:49.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But it's so cold around \Nthe Demon King's castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:52.33,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.92,0:19:55.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's already feeling discouraged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.72,0:20:02.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.43,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,What a carefree girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:08.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold. I don't want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:10.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She's moaning in her sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:14.06,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that cold around \Nthe Demon King's castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.65,0:20:23.20,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ende, where the castle is, is located at the \Nvery northernmost end of the continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.66,0:20:27.16,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,We went through a lot in that place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.12,0:20:29.33,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,A lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:38.54,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is awkward.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:42.13,DefaultItalics,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll wake Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.55,0:20:46.39,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren. Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:51.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,She won't wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:56.56,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Fern. Is she a good master?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.48,0:20:58.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:01.03,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:06.95,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All she does is drag me around \Nwhile she searches for magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.20,0:21:14.00,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But she does seem interested in getting \Nto know Mr. Himmel and his companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:19.54,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps she's not very interested in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.46,0:21:23.26,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren only took me on as an apprentice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:26.88,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,because she promised Mr. Heiter she would.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.76,0:21:29.80,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:34.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But she's such a strange person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.60,0:21:39.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,After we began traveling together, \Nshe started giving me birthday presents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:42.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Normally she seems so disinterested in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.49,0:21:48.66,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what she's thinking. \NShe's so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:21:57.62,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, you're not going \Nto stay in the royal capital?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.29,0:22:00.08,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to keep traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.08,0:22:01.54,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.54,0:22:03.09,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be nice and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.84,0:22:06.26,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to take on an apprentice?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.26,0:22:09.18,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Traveling is better when you \Nhave someone to talk to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.55,0:22:11.85,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.85,0:22:14.68,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I taught them, they'd die in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.31,0:22:21.56,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, that's not how relationships work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.94,0:22:23.90,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.90,0:22:29.03,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,My adventure with you wasn't even \None one-hundredth of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.78,0:22:31.57,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You must understand that, Eisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.57,0:22:33.12,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.24,0:22:38.33,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. That's enough depressing talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:42.04,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Today is a day for celebrating. Let's drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.04,0:22:45.05,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,You just want a reason to drink, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:46.59,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,You saw right through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.59,0:22:49.18,Flashback,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're always drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.18,0:22:50.84,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You corrupt priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.64,0:22:56.47,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Fern...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.31,0:22:59.98,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,She's a good master.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.56,0:23:03.90,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.44,0:23:10.78,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Eisen, you're really not coming with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.24,0:23:12.24,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.57,0:23:16.99,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,I told you before, I'd only get in your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.16,0:23:19.25,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.62,0:23:23.42,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You remember how to get to Ende, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:26.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. First we travel through the Wille region,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.13,0:23:30.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and then we cross Riegel Canyon and pass \Nthrough the northern lands checkpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:33.89,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask this of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.30,0:23:36.26,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.89,0:23:39.73,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,It took us ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.85,0:23:43.10,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.10,0:23:47.86,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be following the same path Mr. Himmel's\Nparty took to the Demon King's castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.39,0:24:15.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.39,0:24:18.68,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a mere ten-year adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.93,0:24:22.48,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,And you alright
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:24.98,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.77,0:24:31.86,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Trailing along deserted train tracks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.86,0:24:34.20,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Crying excessively
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.78,0:24:37.37,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Wanting you to smile
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.37,0:24:43.42,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I hold on to memories I'd like to keep fresh
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.42,0:24:47.13,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.13,0:24:49.88,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,With words more precious than a goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.88,0:24:55.55,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Unremarkable yet special
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.55,0:24:59.10,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,See, things that couldn't have been
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.10,0:25:02.14,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Seen if it weren't for these eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.14,0:25:06.90,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Why? They begin to overflow
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.90,0:25:12.99,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if I were to be born again
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.99,0:25:18.83,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely choose this place once more
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.83,0:25:24.83,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we were to meet again
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.83,0:25:30.59,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never let you go, I'd choose the present
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.59,0:25:33.55,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no promises were made
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.55,0:25:36.47,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm lost in days of loneliness
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.47,0:25:42.64,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,Those tears will be alright, \Ndawn will surely break
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.64,0:25:45.31,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,I’m whispering our lullaby
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.31,0:25:49.23,Songs_ED,ED LYRICS,0000,0000,0000,,for you to come back home
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.23,0:25:52.44,Default,CHILD,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I can become a powerful warrior?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.98,0:25:53.15,DefaultOverlap,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I'll haunt you after I'm dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.40,0:25:54.78,DefaultTop,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You really do collect a lot of odd spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.44,0:25:55.90,Default,VILLAGER,0000,0000,0000,,Travelers, may I have a moment of your time?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.94,0:25:55.90,DefaultOverlap,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why haven't you defeated the dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.90,0:25:57.78,Default,EISEN,0000,0000,0000,,You're searching for someone, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.53,0:25:57.78,DefaultOverlap,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
